  "prompt": "What is potassium sorbate?",
  "response": "Potassium sorbate is a chemical compound with the formula C6H7KO2. It is a potassium salt of sorbic acid and is commonly used as a food preservative. It helps to extend the shelf life of various food products by inhibiting the growth of molds, yeasts, and some bacteria. Potassium sorbate is considered safe for consumption and is approved for use in many countries, including the United States and the European Union. It is often found in products such as cheese, yogurt, wine, baked goods, and dried fruits.",
